UAL.name: United Airlines Holdings, Inc.
UAL.tagline: Fast-growing carrierâ€”$32B market cap, stock +180% in 12 months, aggressive expansion
UAL.overview: United Airlines is one of the world's largest airlines, headquartered in Chicago. Under CEO Scott Kirby (highest-paid U.S. airline CEO at $33.9M in 2024), United's stock surged 180%+ over 12 monthsâ€”more than any other U.S. carrier. In 2024, United operated the most flights and carried the most customers in its history. The airline is growing domestic capacity 5.7% in 2025 vs industry average of ~2%. Kirby projects industry consolidation to eventually result in only two major players.

UNIPHORE.name: Uniphore
UNIPHORE.tagline: The Business AI Company â€“ Leading Enterprise AI & Conversational Automation Platform
UNIPHORE.overview: Uniphore is a leading B2B AI-native company providing the Business AI Cloud platform. Founded in 2008 by Umesh Sachdev and Ravi Saraogi, and headquartered in Palo Alto, California (with a dual HQ in Chennai, India), the company enables businesses to rapidly adopt, significantly transform, and immediately unlock value through AI. With a multimodal architecture combining Generative AI, Knowledge AI, Emotion AI, and Workflow Automation, Uniphore helps organizations deploy agentic AI across every enterprise function while ensuring data sovereignty and security. As of October 2025, Uniphore has achieved unicorn status with a $2.5 billion valuation and has raised over $987 million in total funding.

investors.name: Business AI Cloud: Sovereign, composable, and secure platform for deploying agentic AI across enterprise functions.
